I think in C++1y we&#x27;ll be able to define a function &#x27;foreach&#x27; that we can use like:<p><pre><code>    foreach(data, []<class T>(const T & item) {
        ofile << item << std::endl;
    });
</code></pre>
This should eliminate the potential implicit conversion to temp. But I&#x27;m not sure it&#x27;s seriously better than the original range based for with auto.
